---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
	title="Capabilities"
	description="What OkArthur does: data and AI strategy, digital platforms and digital twins, and capital delivery transformation across the GCC."
>
	<div class="page-head">
		<h1 class="page-title">Capabilities</h1>
		<p class="lede">
			Three areas where digital and data decide whether a capital programme
			lands: what you decide to build, what you build it on, and how the
			organisation around it works.
		</p>
	</div>

	<section class="capability reveal">
		<h2 class="capability-title tick">Data and AI strategy</h2>
		<p>
			Making data and AI useful in live capital delivery rather than in a
			pilot. Strategy, governance, and the ownership and decision rights that
			make it stick once the consultants leave.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="capability reveal">
		<h2 class="capability-title tick">Digital platforms and digital twins</h2>
		<p>
			Platforms, digital twins and asset data built to survive handover.
			Procurement-ready, operable, and designed for the people who inherit
			them at commissioning rather than the people who specified them.
		</p>
	</section>

	<section class="capability reveal">
		<h2 class="capability-title tick">Capital delivery transformation</h2>
		<p>
			Operating models, systems engineering and programme governance across
			multi-agency delivery. Shared standards, clear roles, and benefits
			measures that carry through mobilisation and into early operations.
		</p>
	</section>
</Base>
